to translate your ggplot code into Seaborn or Plot9 or whatever you want. So this kind of, like,

00:16:35.719 --> 00:16:40.520
I think is a perfect value-based learning tool, right? To get you over that hump and give you

00:16:40.520 --> 00:16:45.239
that confidence that you can actually build it, right? It gives you value, provides integration

00:16:45.239 --> 00:16:49.640
options, gives your employer value because it does things that they can't really do right now.

00:16:49.640 --> 00:16:54.280
